				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_508340">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				<div class="bbcode_postedby">
					<img src="images/misc/quote_icon.png" alt="Quote" /> Originally Posted by <strong>Shawn</strong>
					<a href="showthread.php?s=eb5c8fb3657c0c320fcb2ed65155ac46&amp;p=508328#post508328" rel="nofollow"><img class="inlineimg" src="images/buttons/viewpost-right.png" alt="View Post" /></a>
				</div>
				<div class="message">Most employers will work to help employees get help with addiction issues.  If someone has eaten themselves into type II diabetes an employer will help that person due to medical consequences of that disease.  How is drug or alcohol addiction any different?  There should be consequences to drug use, but those consequences should involve treatment.</div>
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>While I agree that it's a cool thing for employers to help their people with various issues, it isn't their <i>responsibility </i>to do so. Either way, I hope that Adams gets the counseling or treatment that he needs. Addicts will say and do anything to get what they want, so I hope that it hasn't come to that in his life.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
